1
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:14,250
If the Wan Hai case
was really mishandled,

2
00:00:14,510 --> 00:00:15,810
I'd be doomed.

3
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:17,980
I think a storm is coming

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,850
for Dongping's
political and legal system.

5
00:00:23,510 --> 00:00:25,170
This Task Force is coming in hard,

6
00:00:25,920 --> 00:00:28,050
not just here to check a box.

7
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:30,050
You mean

8
00:00:30,510 --> 00:00:31,620
this isn't just a passing gust?

9
00:00:31,830 --> 00:00:34,450
Each time, it seemed like
the sky was falling.

10
00:00:35,070 --> 00:00:36,690
Everyone thought
everything's gonna change.

11
00:00:36,710 --> 00:00:37,260
But what happened?

12
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:38,050
Dongping

13
00:00:38,470 --> 00:00:40,010
stayed the same.

14
00:00:41,280 --> 00:00:42,260
So what are you gonna do?

15
00:00:42,470 --> 00:00:44,050
Come forward to the Task Force,

16
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:45,450
or

17
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:46,500
file a report?

18
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,410
Some people

19
00:00:48,430 --> 00:00:49,860
just start blindly ratting others out

20
00:00:51,030 --> 00:00:53,090
at the first sign of trouble.

21
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:21,640
[In the Name of Justice]

22
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:24,640
[Episode 29]

23
00:02:28,910 --> 00:02:30,010
Talk to me.

24
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:33,410
Bro, you're carrying
three fake passports.

25
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:34,850
Where were you planning to go?

26
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:40,850
Hong Liang.

27
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:42,340
I...

28
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:43,890
was wrong.

29
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:44,820
I messed up.

30
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,380
As a public official,

31
00:02:47,430 --> 00:02:48,220
I shouldn't have

32
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:51,100
bought fake passports.

33
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,890
It was wrong. A clear violation.

34
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:54,380
I'll be honest with you.

35
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:56,450
I was planning to go to Hong Kong

36
00:02:56,870 --> 00:02:58,060
to get some insurance

37
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,450
for my kid.

38
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,260
If I told the organization about this,

39
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,130
they'd never approve it.

40
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,100
And I couldn't talk to anyone else
about it either.

41
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,380
But for today's matter,

42
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,100
I should probably thank you.

43
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,820
If you hadn't stopped me,

44
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:15,010
I would've made an even bigger mistake.

45
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:16,450
It would've gone way too far.

46
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,060
You're welcome.

47
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:18,500
We're even now.

48
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,450
I believe that you must also understand

49
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,890
that we didn't invite you here today

50
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:27,290
just because of
those three fake passports

51
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,170
or your attempt to
leave the country secretly.

52
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,220
A couple of days ago,

53
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,290
someone

54
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,130
sat exactly where you are now.

55
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:39,500
He named you.

56
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:42,010
And you know him well.

57
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,570
An old subordinate of yours.

58
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,410
His name is

59
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:45,660
Jiang Hongjun.

60
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:47,940
Say no more.

61
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:50,890
He threw me under the bus,

62
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,010
didn't he?

63
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,450
Let's put it this way,

64
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:55,820
if you hadn't had solid evidence,

65
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,730
you wouldn't have arrested him.

66
00:03:58,590 --> 00:04:00,220
If he hadn't given me away,

67
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:02,010
you wouldn't have

68
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,610
brought me in.

69
00:04:05,470 --> 00:04:08,220
But my question is, Hong Liang,

70
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:10,340
do you think

71
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,010
I'm that kind of person?

72
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:16,250
Mr. Jiang jumped me all the way

73
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:18,290
to my position today.

74
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:21,730
Other people might not know who I am,

75
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:23,700
but you do.

76
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:43,850
People in charge

77
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:45,610
are always one step ahead.

78
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:49,220
Mr. Jiang,
sorry to keep you waiting.

79
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,100
Fortunately, it doesn't matter

80
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,580
early or late.

81
00:04:58,510 --> 00:05:00,140
We still got time to
enjoy the view together.

82
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:01,930
Sir,

83
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:04,140
how many years

84
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:06,170
has it been

85
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:08,730
since we parted ways in Dongping?

86
00:05:11,630 --> 00:05:12,780
Maybe over ten years?

87
00:05:14,310 --> 00:05:15,170
We've both aged.

88
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,850
Well, I've aged.

89
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,370
But you still

90
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:24,140
look sharp as ever.

91
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,580
Back then, I thought

92
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:29,700
we'd go our separate ways forever,

93
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,900
never crossing paths again.

94
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,490
Wheel never stops turning.

95
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,540
You know what that means?

96
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:38,050
Sir?

97
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,460
It means

98
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:42,020
we were always bound to meet again.

99
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,900
But no matter how the wheel turns,

100
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,850
a cat is still a cat,
and a rat is still a rat.

101
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:51,660
Mr. Yu.

102
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:55,020
When people get older,

103
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:56,490
they should accept it.

104
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:59,250
Every generation has
its own way of life

105
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,660
and its own fate.

106
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,810
Let the kids

107
00:06:03,430 --> 00:06:04,900
walk their own path.

108
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,900
I heard that

109
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:09,850
you got a manor,

110
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:11,700
raising horses and planting flowers,

111
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,100
living the good life.

112
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:14,980
That's the way to
enjoy your later years.

113
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,490
Be content and happy.

114
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,220
Yuan told you this, right?

115
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,610
Speaking of Jiang Hongjun,

116
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,220
he's actually a good kid at heart.

117
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:33,980
Very good.

118
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,850
I don't know if you still remember

119
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:37,170
the 829 case.

120
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:40,660
That criminal was wild back then.

121
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,700
With two homemade five-shot guns

122
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,220
and hundreds of rounds on him,

123
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,290
he shot it out with us.

124
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:49,170
I was leading the team that day.

125
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,490
I kicked the door open myself.

126
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,170
Bullets

127
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:54,540
were flying right past my ear.

128
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:55,900
And Jiang Hongjun

129
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,100
tackled the guy on the spot.

130
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,780
That's how he earned
his second-class merit.

131
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:02,700
We promoted him

132
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,020
to captain after that.

133
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:05,980
That is to say,

134
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:07,850
Mr. Sun, you think

135
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,050
really highly of him.

136
00:07:09,310 --> 00:07:10,580
Back then, absolutely.

137
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,050
Then help us analyze it,

138
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:13,100
since you know him well,

139
00:07:14,190 --> 00:07:16,250
what does it take

140
00:07:16,270 --> 00:07:18,020
for a brilliant policeman like him

141
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:18,580
to end up

142
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,490
in this very seat you're in now?

143
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,020
This seat...

144
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,810
I'm not convicted yet.

145
00:07:26,270 --> 00:07:26,610
Yes.

146
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:30,170
How did he get here?

147
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,020
Let me put it this way,

148
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,730
after he became

149
00:07:36,390 --> 00:07:37,220
the captain,

150
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:38,850
he started forming

151
00:07:38,870 --> 00:07:40,850
his own little circle.

152
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,780
His social network
got extremely complicated.

153
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:45,580
Honestly,

154
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,850
I wasn't really sure

155
00:07:48,950 --> 00:07:50,660
who he's been spending time with

156
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,220
or what kind of circles
he's been involved in.

157
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:01,700
Got it.

158
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,020
So you're saying that the two of you

159
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:06,980
gradually had less private contact.

160
00:08:07,390 --> 00:08:09,540
But still, you were

161
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,220
superior and subordinate

162
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,580
or we can say, close as brothers,

163
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,490
how could he

164
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:17,780
end up sitting here

165
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:19,850
and pointing you out?

166
00:08:27,630 --> 00:08:30,020
I think maybe it's because

167
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:34,530
I became an obstacle on his way up.

168
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:36,060
How so?

169
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:39,130
When it came to
joining the Party committee,

170
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:40,580
I voted

171
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,820
against him several times.

172
00:08:43,910 --> 00:08:44,460
Why?

173
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,180
Because he's too street-smart.

174
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,530
I thought he needed more tempering.

175
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:51,250
Of course, I told him this directly too.

176
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:53,180
I said, "You can't be so street-smart.

177
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,250
You're a public servant.

178
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:57,850
You're a law enforcer.

179
00:08:58,630 --> 00:09:00,730
You can't always talk about
personal favors and connections."

180
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,770
Maybe because of these things,

181
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,220
he came to

182
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,420
resent me.

183
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,300
He even said that

184
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,130
it was me

185
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:14,180
who pulled him onto this ship.

186
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,820
And more than once.

187
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:20,010
That really pains me.

188
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:23,010
So from now on,

189
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,650
I won't respond to
any of Jiang Hongjun's accusations

190
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,060
against me.

191
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,490
Because they're all false.

192
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:37,130
Sir,

193
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,060
I know

194
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,300
why you asked

195
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,820
to see me

196
00:09:43,510 --> 00:09:44,340
today.

197
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:46,220
Actually,

198
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:50,010
I haven't really been involved in much
these past few years.

199
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,820
The tree may wish to remain still,

200
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,010
but the wind will not cease.

201
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:57,770
Yu Tiancheng, don't play dumb with me.

202
00:09:58,030 --> 00:09:59,490
If you really wanted to retire,

203
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:01,580
you wouldn't have stayed just
because of a few words from Jiang Yuan.

204
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:04,700
You think I don't know
what kind of person you are?

205
00:10:05,790 --> 00:10:07,130
For 50% profit,

206
00:10:07,870 --> 00:10:09,340
you'd already dare to take risks.

207
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:11,650
If it's for 100% profit,

208
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:14,300
you'll be riding roughshod over the law.

209
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:17,010
And now for that copper-nickel mine,

210
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:20,980
you've killed and set fire.

211
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:24,820
But let me remind you,

212
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:27,060
this isn't ten years ago.

213
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:29,340
Party discipline and national law
are not to be violated.

214
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:31,220
If you try those tricks again,

215
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:32,370
I believe

216
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:36,530
you'll lose everything.

217
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,370
And you want to drag my family

218
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:42,980
down with you again?

219
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:52,300
Dad!

220
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,700
I did something bad!

221
00:10:57,550 --> 00:11:00,420
I did something bad, Dad!

222
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,580
I hit someone with my car
and killed them.

223
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,460
What should I do?

224
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,250
You bastard!

225
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:10,420
Where did you get the car?

226
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:12,250
Dad...

227
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:13,730
Who let you drive?

228
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:14,820
Hello?

229
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,490
This is Yu Tiancheng.

230
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:23,850
Your son hit and killed someone.

231
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:26,770
He's drunk.

232
00:11:27,510 --> 00:11:27,980
Unlicensed.

233
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,730
And killed someone.

234
00:11:31,870 --> 00:11:32,700
Mr. Jiang,

235
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:35,730
this should be
at least seven years in prison.

236
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:38,650
We are now on Pingnan Avenue.

237
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,130
Come now

238
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:44,250
before I call the police.

239
00:11:45,550 --> 00:11:47,180
Come here now, Mr. Jiang.

240
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,130
We can say

241
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,300
I'm the one who hit the person.

242
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:57,850
Yu Tiancheng,

243
00:12:00,510 --> 00:12:02,420
I didn't expect you to
rack your brains so much

244
00:12:03,870 --> 00:12:05,730
and target Jiang Yuan in the end.

245
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,130
Have you thought about the consequences?

246
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:09,130
What?

247
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:10,340
Mr. Jiang,

248
00:12:10,790 --> 00:12:13,420
don't you care about
your own son's consequences?

249
00:12:15,390 --> 00:12:16,820
You'll understand once you get here.

250
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:30,130
Mr. Jiang.

251
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,180
According to investigation,

252
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,820
the driver of the accident vehicle
wasn't Jiang Yuan.

253
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:34,130
You can take him home now.

254
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,300
We'll need him to come back later
for a statement.

255
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:40,610
Sister.

256
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:41,890
Slowly.

257
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:15,850
Sir,

258
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:18,850
what new energy?

259
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:23,180
How could an old man like me
understand any of that?

260
00:13:24,870 --> 00:13:26,300
Yuan is knowledgeable

261
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,220
and ambitious.

262
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,700
He wants to make something of himself.

263
00:13:32,390 --> 00:13:33,420
I'm really

264
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:35,530
just accompanying him.

265
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,650
Also, that Wan Hai case

266
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,820
isn't something
that I could ever come up with,

267
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,890
even if I rack my brains.

268
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:45,250
I know my son.

269
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:48,730
If it weren't for you
fanning the flames behind him,

270
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,060
would he have done all that?

271
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:51,650
You used him!

272
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:02,980
Okay, Mr. Yu.

273
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:06,940
What exactly do you want me to do

274
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:09,700
to let Jiang Yuan go,

275
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,490
to let my family go?

276
00:14:15,510 --> 00:14:16,180
Sir,

277
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,300
who's letting who go here?

278
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:25,820
That mine was mine to begin with.

279
00:14:26,510 --> 00:14:28,060
Things have gotten to this point,

280
00:14:29,670 --> 00:14:31,010
none of us can stop now.

281
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,580
Me and my students,

282
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,220
including you,

283
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:38,700
have already been dragged into this.

284
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,420
And it was your Jiang Yuan

285
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,060
who dragged us all in.

286
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:43,730
Wasn't it?

287
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,100
Let me tell you the truth.

288
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:56,650
Jiang Yuan

289
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,130
